Jan 26 2005	Used to be a find	About seven years ago, I starting making short trips to London to go antiquing. I would usually stay at the Ivanhoe, and found it basic, but clean, neat and friendly and very inexpensive (around 67 pounds a night, incl tax and cont. breakfast). The people who worked there and managed the place were very pleasant to deal with. The location is terrific, as there are lots of restaurants and shopping nearby, and I didn't have to be frightened to be alone. There was a middle eastern restaurant with great food downstairs that sayed open pretty late, and I liked to go there too. So, Frommers used to be right. It was a find.I was so dissappointed when about three years ago, I brought my family with me to stay there for two nights. The place had been sold to new owners, who have no idea what even &quot;basic&quot; service is. Piles of old laundry were on all of the narrow stair landings. (there is no elevator; imagine navigating your suitcase around these piles) They didn't service the rooms at all while we were there. When we arrived, there was only one towel for all four of us. I had to go searching through their hall closets in search of more towels or clean linens. When we were checking out, the desk guy was very slow because he was engrossed in some LOUD horrid TV show starring a very fowl mouthed, large breasted, drunken, rude American woman -- a TV show he had playing in their very small first floor landing &quot;lobby&quot;. I've read the other reviews and can imagine that if the current management kept up the same dismal service we experienced on our last visit to the Ivanhoe, then it is likely that they have let the hotel get run down and even become full of fleas. How sad.Keep shopping; there are lots of other great places to stay in London.	
