Apr 6 2004	Good value and great location	This hotel only costs around ?70 per night. It is in an excellent location. Considering you can stay in a 4* hotel in the West End and be kept awake all night by Police sirens this accomodation is very quiet as the restaurants close at about midnight and there is no further noise. Admittedly the accomodation is basic but for the price, location and peace it is a very good base to stay in London. I have stayed in many 4 and 5 * hotels and paid a minimum of ?140 per night for a few extra frills but do you really need a health club and an on site restaurant and bar when London has so many to offer? I would not hesitate to recommend this.	
