Jun 20 2003	Ivanhoe Suite hotel is not the great value as claimed by Frommers	My boyfriend and I recently spent 3 weeks touring England, Scotland, &amp; Ireland. Our trip started off with 2 nights in London and the trip ended with one night in London. The last hotel we stayed in was recommended by Frommer's as a &quot;great value with an excellent location&quot;. Well the location was good (hard to get to though since it was in an area that didn't permit driving) but the hotel was a dump. If you blink you will miss the entrance to this hotel. We rang the buzzer and knocked on the door for 10 minutes before someone let us in. You are immediately escorted up a very narrow flight of stairs to a reception area no bigger than a guest bathroom. After being left there to wait for the manager who took 15 minutes to arrive we were then escorted to our room. The room looked like it was maybe cleaned 2 a week and the bathroom was cramped and getting the shower to work took no less than a miracle. The worst part is that the rooms are located directly above two restaurants that are open late into the evening. Did I mention that the restaurants offer musical talent that plays until midnight? I definitely don't know when the Frommer review was written but I would not recommend this place to anyone.	
